decks.notes: This deck focuses on ramping up mana quickly to combo off with Primeval Titan and various land synergies. By utilizing effects that untap lands, such as Amulet of Vigor, players can generate a large amount of mana in a single turn to search for key lands or spells with Primeval Titan or Green Sun's Zenith. By setting up a strong mana base with powerful utility lands like Urza's Saga and Vesuva, the deck aims to overwhelm opponents with massive creatures and game-winning combos.

This Boros Aggro deck focuses on quickly overwhelming the opponent with aggressive creatures and burn spells. The key strategy is to establish a fast board presence with creatures like Ragavan, Nimble Pilferer and Phlage, Titan of Fire's Fury, backed up by removal spells like Lightning Bolt and Galvanic Discharge. Ajani, Nacatl Pariah helps to boost your creatures and close out games, while Fable of the Mirror-Breaker can provide extra card advantage. The deck also includes ways to disrupt the opponent with Ranger-Captain of Eos and Static Prison. Overall, the deck aims to win the game quickly through a combination of creature aggression and direct damage.

The deck focuses on using Cascade mechanics to quickly generate value and overwhelm the opponent with powerful spells like Crashing Footfalls and Shardless Agent. By playing Leyline cards and utilizing multicolor lands, the deck aims to maintain a consistent mana base while still being able to cast a variety of spells. With a mix of creatures and spells, the deck can apply pressure early on and maintain momentum throughout the game. The key strategy is to cascade into impactful spells while keeping up the aggression to quickly close out the game.

The deck focuses on quickly deploying disruptive creatures to control the game while applying pressure on the opponent's life total. By utilizing Aether Vial and Ephemerate, the deck can efficiently trigger powerful enter-the-battlefield abilities multiple times. This strategy aims to disrupt the opponent's game plan and gain incremental advantages through card advantage and tempo plays. Additionally, the deck features a mix of removal spells and resilient threats to deal with a variety of threats, making it a versatile and challenging opponent to face in the Modern format.

This deck focuses on quickly filling the graveyard with cards to enable graveyard recursion and trigger powerful effects. By utilizing cards like Narcomoeba, Golgari Thug, and Stinkweed Imp to dredge cards into the graveyard, the deck can bring back powerful creatures like Prized Amalgam and Silversmote Ghoul. Other cards like Ox of Agonas and Creeping Chill provide additional value by utilizing the graveyard. The goal is to quickly overwhelm the opponent with a constant stream of threats and utilize the graveyard as a resource to win the game.

The deck focuses on using aggressive creatures and disruptive spells to control the board and put pressure on the opponent. It utilizes cards like Thoughtseize and Inquisition of Kozilek to disrupt the opponent's hand, while creatures like Tarmogoyf and Ragavan, Nimble Pilferer provide a quick clock. The deck also includes removal spells like Fatal Push and Unholy Heat to deal with threats. Additionally, cards like Wrenn and Six provide card advantage and recursion. The mana base is focused on consistency and includes powerful lands like Urza's Saga and Boseiju, Who Endures.
